title_block.title: Memory Card for Z80 Modular Computer

comment.value: Also RAM bank (0 or 1) can be selected by hardware or software.
CPU can disable ROM and work with full 64KB RAM, allowing bootstrap for CP/M.
User can select which 16KB block of ROM will be used via jumpers (blocks 0, 1, 2 or 3).
During initialization, bottom 16KB are ROM and the remaining 48KB are RAM.
